name: ASCVDI10
title: ASCVD I10
purpose:
(Clinical Focus: Definition:This value set intends to capture all ICD-10 CM diagnosis codes that represent atherosclerotic heart disease (CAD), Peripheral Artery Disease (PAD) and Cerebrovascular diseases (CVD) which are also atherosclerotic in origin),(Data Element Scope: CONDITION: CLINICAL_DRIVER:),(Inclusion Criteria: "CAD: Angina- I20*; Acute MI - I21*; Subsequent MI- I22*; Complications Following MI -I23*; Other Acute Ischemic Heart Dz- I24*; Chronic Ischemic Heart Dz- I25*, H/o MI, H/o CABG, H/o stent in place, old MI
CVD: Transient cerebral ischemic attacks and related syndromes- G45*; Vascular syndromes of brain in cerebrovascular diseases-G46*; Cerebral Infarction-I63*; Occlusion and stenosis of precerebral arteries, not resulting in cerebral infarction-I65*; Occlusion and stenosis of cerebral arteries, not resulting in cerebral infarction-I66*;  Cerebral Atherosclerosis-I67.2; Sequelae of Cerebral Infarction-I69.3*
PAD: Atherosclerosis- I70*; "),(Exclusion Criteria: ICD-10 and SCT  codes that are not representative of atherosclerosis: Coronary artery spasm angina-87343002)
